    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith [`uv`](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) you can create a python script with automatic dependency and venv management using the following shebang:\n\n```sh\n#!/usr/bin/env -S uv run --script\n```\n\nSee https://docs.astral.sh/uv/guides/scripts/#using-a-shebang-to-create-an-executable-file\n\nHowever, neovim doesn't automatically detect these scripts as having a `python` filetype.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should detect such scripts as having a `python` filetype.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-08T22:04:52Z",
